ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great news! You have <strong>Websites + Marketing Free</strong> on GoDaddy — that's perfect. However, this means you <strong>don't have a traditional Web Hosting/cPanel</strong> plan, so we can't upload the HTML file the usual way.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">But don't worry — there's an even <strong>easier path</strong> for you! 👇</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Your Two Options</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option A — Use GoDaddy's Website Builder (Free, easiest)</strong>
GoDaddy's "Websites + Marketing Free" has a drag-and-drop builder. I can guide you to paste our content into it. No file uploading needed.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option B — Use GitHub Pages (Free, and our HTML file works perfectly)</strong>
A free service called GitHub Pages lets you host our ready-made HTML file directly — and then connect it to jurisnair.com. Takes about 15 minutes and I'll guide every click.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5"></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">My honest recommendation is <strong>Option B</strong> — because our HTML file is already beautifully designed and ready to go. Option A would mean rebuilding everything inside GoDaddy's builder from scratch.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
