ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Understood! Let's use GoDaddy's builder. Here's the thing though — since the builder is drag-and-drop, we can't directly import our HTML file. Instead, I'll guide you to set it up using GoDaddy's tools, and we'll recreate your content (which I already have ready) inside it.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 1 — Open Your Website Builder</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Log in to <strong><a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="http://www.godaddy.com/">www.godaddy.com</a></strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>My Products</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Websites + Marketing Free</strong>, click the blue <strong>Manage</strong> button</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This will open your GoDaddy Website Builder dashboard</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Once it opens, tell me what you see on screen</strong> — for example:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Does it ask you to <strong>pick a template</strong>?</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Or does it show an <strong>existing blank website</strong>?</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Or something else?</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Just describe what's on your screen and I'll tell you exactly what to click next! 🙂</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
