ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Perfect! You're in the right place. Now let's get your website going.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 1 — Open the Website Editor</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Look for one of these buttons on your screen:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A button that says <strong>"Edit Website"</strong> or <strong>"Edit Site"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Or <strong>"Customize"</strong> or <strong>"Get Started"</strong></li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Click whichever one you see</strong> and tell me what appears next.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Also, one quick question while you do that:</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
