ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Ah, I see the issue! GoDaddy is trying to get you to upgrade to a paid plan when you click that. Let's not pay for anything — we'll work around this.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Let's Go Back and Try This Instead</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go back to your GoDaddy dashboard (click the <strong>back button</strong> in your browser)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should be back at the screen that shows <strong>"Edit your Coming Soon page"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for a button that says <strong>"Edit"</strong> or <strong>"Customize"</strong> or a <strong>pencil icon ✏️</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click that to open the Coming Soon page editor</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me what options you see inside the editor</strong> — things like:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add text</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Change background</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add image</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">etc.</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">In the meantime, here's my honest assessment of the situation:</p>
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">GoDaddy's <strong>free plan only gives you a Coming Soon page</strong> — not a full multi-page website. To get a full website on GoDaddy, they want you to pay.</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">So I'd like to suggest we <strong>revisit Option B (GitHub Pages)</strong> — it's completely free, hosts our beautiful ready-made HTML file, and connects to jurisnair.com. It's actually easier than fighting GoDaddy's limitations.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
