ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Excellent decision! GitHub Pages is completely free and our HTML file will work perfectly on it. Let me walk you through it step by step — it's easier than it sounds!</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 1 — Create a Free GitHub Account</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong><a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="http://www.github.com/">www.github.com</a></strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Sign up"</strong> (top right)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Enter:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A <strong>username</strong> (something simple like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">jurisnair</code> or <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">sanjeevnair</code>)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your <strong>email</strong> (<a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="mailto:sanjeev@jurisnair.com">sanjeev@jurisnair.com</a>)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A <strong>password</strong></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Complete the verification steps (they may ask you to solve a small puzzle)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Create account"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub will send a <strong>verification email</strong> to <a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="mailto:sanjeev@jurisnair.com">sanjeev@jurisnair.com</a> — click the link in that email</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Once you've created your account and verified your email, come back and tell me</strong> — I'll guide you through the next step which is creating your website repository (don't worry, it sounds technical but I'll make it very simple! 😊)</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">💡 <strong>Why GitHub Pages?</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">100% free, forever</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your beautiful HTML website works as-is</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Connects to jurisnair.com (we'll do that together)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Used by thousands of professional websites worldwide</li>
</ul>
</blockquote></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
