ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Perfect! That's the fastest way to sign up.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Now tell me:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>What username did GitHub assign you?</strong> (it shows at the top right corner of the screen, or under your profile icon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Are you currently logged in and can you see the GitHub dashboard?</strong> (it usually shows a home screen with a left sidebar)</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Once I know that, we'll move to <strong>Step 2 — creating your website repository</strong> (think of it as a folder on GitHub that will hold your website file). 🙂</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
