ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Perfect! You're all set. Now let's create your website folder on GitHub.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 2 — Create Your Repository (Website Folder)</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">On your GitHub dashboard, look for a <strong>green button</strong> that says <strong>"New"</strong> on the left side — click it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a <strong>"Create a new repository"</strong> page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Fill in as follows:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Repository name:</strong> type exactly this → <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">sanjeevnair75.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Description:</strong> <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Juris Nair Website</code> (optional but good to add)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Make sure <strong>"Public"</strong> is selected (not Private)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tick the box that says ✅ <strong>"Add a README file"</strong></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down and click the green <strong>"Create repository"</strong> button</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">💡 <strong>Why this exact name?</strong> GitHub Pages requires the repository to be named <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yourusername.github.io</code> — this is what activates the free website hosting automatically!</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me once you've created it and I'll guide you to upload your HTML file next!</strong> 🙂</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
