ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great job! 🎉 Now let's upload your website file.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 3 — Upload Your HTML File</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should now see your repository page (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">sanjeevnair75.github.io</code>)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for a link that says <strong>"Add file"</strong> — click it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A dropdown appears — click <strong>"Upload files"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a box that says <strong>"Drag files here or choose your files"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"choose your files"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find the <strong>index.html</strong> file we created — it should be on your <strong>Desktop</strong> or in your <strong>Downloads</strong> folder</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select it and click <strong>Open</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Wait for it to upload — you'll see the filename appear on screen</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to where it says <strong>"Commit changes"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Just leave everything as is and click the green <strong>"Commit changes"</strong> button</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me once that's done!</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your website will then be live at <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong> within 1-2 minutes — and after that we'll connect it to <strong>jurisnair.com</strong> so it shows your proper domain. Almost there! 🙂</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
