<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 4 — Check Your Website is Live</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open a <strong>new browser tab</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Type: <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong> and press Enter</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should see your <strong>Juris Nair website</strong> live!</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me what you see</strong> — if it shows the website, we're ready to connect it to jurisnair.com! 🙂</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">⏳ If it shows a <strong>404 error</strong>, don't panic — sometimes GitHub takes 2-3 minutes to activate. Wait a moment and refresh the page.</p>
