ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Almost there! This means GitHub is showing the README file instead of your website. We just need to do one small fix — delete the README file so that GitHub picks up your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> instead.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 5 — Delete the README File</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go back to your GitHub repository tab</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should see two files listed — <strong>README.md</strong> and <strong>index.html</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click on <strong>README.md</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for a <strong>trash/delete icon 🗑️</strong> on the right side of the screen (it may also appear when you click the <strong>pencil/edit icon</strong> — then look for delete)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>trash icon</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down and click the green <strong>"Commit changes"</strong> button</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Wait <strong>2-3 minutes</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Refresh <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me what you see after refreshing!</strong> Your Juris Nair website should appear. 🎉</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
