ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Congratulations!! 🎉🎉🎉 Your website is LIVE at <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong>!</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Now the final and most important step — connecting it to your proper domain <strong><a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="http://www.jurisnair.com/">www.jurisnair.com</a></strong> so anyone who visits your domain sees your beautiful website!</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Next Step — Connect jurisnair.com to GitHub Pages</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This involves two things:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Tell GitHub</strong> about your domain</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Tell GoDaddy</strong> to point to GitHub</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Part 1 — Tell GitHub Your Domain</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>Settings → Pages</strong> on GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for a box that says <strong>"Custom domain"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Type: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">www.jurisnair.com</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Save"</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me once that's done</strong> and I'll give you the GoDaddy DNS settings to enter — that's the final step! 😊</p>
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">⏳ We're very close now — once both parts are done, anyone typing <strong><a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="http://www.jurisnair.com/">www.jurisnair.com</a></strong> will land directly on your Juris Nair website!</p>
</blockquote></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
