<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Field</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Type</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">CNAME</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Name</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">www</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Value/Points to</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">sanjeevnair75.github.io</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">So in the <strong>Name</strong> field type <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">www</code> — not <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">@</code>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">@</code> is only for the <strong>A records</strong> we'll add after this.</p>
