ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Welcome back, Sanjeev! Great to hear from you and glad the website is live! 😊</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Now, to your question — yes, it is absolutely possible to create email IDs like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">deepakmata@jurisnair.com</code> and <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">rkmaji@jurisnair.com</code>. These are called <strong>custom domain emails</strong> and they look very professional.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">However, there's an important thing to know first:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">The Reality of Custom Domain Emails</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>They are not free.</strong> Here are your main options:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Option</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Cost</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Google Workspace</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">~₹125/user/month</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Most popular, reliable, works like Gmail</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Zoho Mail</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Free</strong> up to 5 users</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Good option for small teams</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>GoDaddy Professional Email</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">~₹199/user/month</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Since your domain is already there</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">My Recommendation — Zoho Mail (Free!)</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">For a small team of 3 people, <strong>Zoho Mail's free plan</strong> is perfect:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Completely free for up to 5 users</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Works with your jurisnair.com domain</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Professional and reliable</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Works on mobile and desktop</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5"></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">I'll guide you step by step whichever you choose! 😊</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
