ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great — DNS has fully propagated! So the issue is something else. Let's check one thing on GitHub.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Check Custom Domain Setting</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong><a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="http://www.github.com/">www.github.com</a></strong> and sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click on <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Settings"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Pages"</strong> on the left sidebar</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for the <strong>"Custom domain"</strong> box</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tell me — what does it show there? Is <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">www.jurisnair.com</code> still entered there?</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Also — does it show any <strong>error message</strong> in red/yellow below the custom domain box? If yes, tell me exactly what it says! 😊</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
