<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">What To Do</h2>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Wait 15-20 minutes</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Come back to <strong>GitHub → Settings → Pages</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The <strong>"Enforce HTTPS"</strong> checkbox should now be clickable</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tick it ✅</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">💡 GitHub uses a service called <strong>Let's Encrypt</strong> to issue free SSL certificates. Once DNS check is successful, it automatically requests the certificate — but it takes a few minutes to be issued and activated!</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Come back in 20 minutes and try again!</strong> 😊</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
