ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great question! Here's my honest suggestion:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">My Recommendation</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Replace the 3 placeholders + Create a dedicated Blog page</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's why:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The current website has <strong>3 placeholder articles</strong> that are generic — replacing them with your <strong>real published work</strong> immediately adds credibility</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">As you write more articles, a <strong>dedicated Blog page</strong> gives them a proper home and keeps the main page clean</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Visitors can read a <strong>short preview</strong> on the home page and click <strong>"Read More"</strong> to go to the full article — this is how professional law firm websites work</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">How It Would Look</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Home Page</strong> — shows your 3 most recent articles as preview cards with title, short excerpt and "Read More" button</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Blog Page</strong> — shows all your articles in full, one by one, neatly formatted</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This is the most professional setup and works really well for a legal practice website! 😊</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Go ahead and share your LinkedIn article links</strong> and I'll get started building it for you! Just paste them here one by one. 🙂</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
