ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes, that's exactly the problem! GitHub cannot read files inside a zip folder — it needs the files uploaded <strong>individually</strong>, not zipped.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Here's How to Fix It</h2>
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 1 — Delete the Zip File from GitHub</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>github.com</strong> and sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click on your repository <strong>sanjeevnair75.github.io</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find the zip file you uploaded — click on it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>trash/delete icon 🗑️</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Commit changes"</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 2 — Extract the Files on Your Computer First</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find the zip file on your computer (Desktop or Downloads)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Right click</strong> on it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select <strong>"Extract All"</strong> or <strong>"Extract Here"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This will create a folder with the individual files inside</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 3 — Upload Files Individually</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go back to your GitHub repository</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Add file" → "Upload files"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open the extracted folder on your computer</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select <strong>all three files</strong> together:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">article-petrochemical-ceasefire.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">linkedin-cover-petrochemical-ceasefire_2.png</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Commit changes"</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Tell me once done and we'll check if the article is live!</strong> 😊</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
