<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 2 — Rename the file on your Computer FIRST</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find the file on your computer (Downloads or Desktop)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Right click</strong> on it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select <strong>"Rename"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it exactly: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">article-petrochemical-ceasefire.html</code></li>
