ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">I'd love to generate a cover image for you, but I need to be upfront — I don't have the ability to generate or create image files (like PNG or JPG) directly.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's what I suggest instead:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Two Easy Options to Create the Cover</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Use Canva (Free, 5 minutes)</strong>
Canva is a free design tool perfect for this. I can give you:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Exact text to use</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Layout instructions</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Color codes matching your website theme</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — I create an HTML/SVG cover</strong>
I design a cover as an HTML file matching your website's dark gold theme — with the GSTAT statistics, title, and a visual element. You can take a screenshot and use it as your cover image.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">My recommendation is <strong>Option 2</strong> — it's instant, matches your website perfectly, and you just take a screenshot to use as the cover image everywhere including LinkedIn!</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
